LXII. l. a. soro olitorio, “the vegetable market.’' Forum originally meant any open space before a building; hence, distinguished by an epithet signifying what was sold therein, ‘⁴ a market-place.'' So forum boarium, “ the cattle market‚” occurs just below.

b. Lanuvii.- a city of Latium near the Appian road, about twenty miles from Rome. After the Latin war (B.c. 340) its only importance was the peculiar sanctity which attached to it as one of the chief seats of the old Latin religion. Its temple of Juno Sospita was held in especial reverence.
